AIO Survey Questions-

1) Q:  Overall, how do you feel Amiga is doing in trying to bring back
our favorite system?
   Answers:  1 = Comodore did better in it's end days.
             2 = Abyssmal, but there's some hope
             3 = Fair, all things considered
             4 = Great!  Keep it up and we'll show those Wintel people.
             5 = I've died and gone to Ami-Heaven!

2) Q:  Do you agree with Amiga's Software only (or mainly) approach?
   Answers:  YES, or NO.

3) Q:  How important is advertizing/marketing to Amiga's future?
   Answers:  1 = Who cares?
             2 = It'd be nice, but it's not really key.
             3 = We do need some, but build a good product and they will come.
             4 = At least as important as the chip they use.
             5 = MORE important then the hardware.

4) Q:  Which chip would you most like to see a new AmigaONE ystem based around?

5)  Q:  Of what you've seen/heard so far of the SDK and new Amiga
Operating Environment, how do you rate it?
    Answers:  1 = Give me Windows, PLEASE!
              2 = I think Linux still has the edge
              3 = Has problems, but still doing good.
              4 = Very good.  Better then I expected.
              5 = o/~ I found my Thril...

Just email your answers (make sure to number them, of course) to: survey@aio.co.uk
The results will be published in a future issue.



